WEBVTT

01:44.271 --> 01:46.356
- Morning.
- Morning.

02:04.708 --> 02:07.169
- Looking for something?
- Yeah.

02:07.169 --> 02:09.588
A hardcover
of <i>Their Eyes Were Watching God.</i>

02:10.797 --> 02:13.258
Hardcover? Yeah. I think we have one.

02:35.405 --> 02:36.406
Thanks.

02:37.366 --> 02:40.077
You know, I actually haven't read
much Hurston.

02:40.077 --> 02:41.161
Yeah, she's great.

02:41.954 --> 02:43.956
It's actually a gift for my professor.

02:43.956 --> 02:45.499
Okay. You're a student.

02:46.041 --> 02:47.209
Getting my PhD.

02:49.253 --> 02:51.672
- Columbia? NYU?
- NYU.

02:51.672 --> 02:54.174
Nice. What's your--
What's your thesis topic?

02:54.174 --> 02:55.634
"Redefining Radicalism:

02:55.634 --> 02:57.553
The Rise of Black Feminism
in American Literature."

02:57.553 --> 02:58.929
Oh, wow.

02:58.929 --> 03:00.597
That's a mouthful.

03:01.890 --> 03:05.227
- How's that going?
- Slowly. Very slowly.

03:05.227 --> 03:06.478
Oh, yeah?

03:06.478 --> 03:08.230
- <i>Irma Thomas</i>...
- Well, I'm impressed.

03:08.230 --> 03:11.567
...<i>"Ruler of my Heart" on</i> WNYC.

03:11.567 --> 03:12.985
That'll be 15 even.

03:12.985 --> 03:14.653
- ...<i>New York public radio.</i>
- Thank you.

03:14.653 --> 03:16.321
<i>I'm John Schaefer,</i>

03:16.321 --> 03:19.992
<i>and if the soul queen of New Orleans
couldn't lighten the mood,</i>

03:19.992 --> 03:21.743
<i>maybe Duke Ellington will.</i>

03:21.743 --> 03:23.245
<i>Here's his classic version</i>

03:23.245 --> 03:27.624
of <i>"In a Sentimental Mood,"
featuring John Coltrane.</i>

03:29.877 --> 03:33.088
There's actually this
little Japanese restaurant on Mott Street.

03:35.966 --> 03:38.302
If you're not doing anything later,
dinner's on me.

03:39.803 --> 03:40.804
Sorry.

03:42.723 --> 03:43.807
No. That's--

03:43.807 --> 03:46.518
- You probably have a boyfriend.
- No, I don't. I'm single.

03:48.270 --> 03:52.316
I'm-I'm single,
and I kinda like being single.

03:52.316 --> 03:54.818
Oh, yeah. No, I totally get that.

03:56.528 --> 03:58.071
Your card's not going through.

03:58.071 --> 03:59.698
I must've maxed it out again.

03:59.698 --> 04:02.534
- Let me see if I have enough cash.
- It's fine. It's fine.

04:06.163 --> 04:08.165
You know what?
Actually just take the book.

04:09.416 --> 04:10.792
No, I couldn't.

04:10.792 --> 04:13.545
- What if someone else came in looking--
- They can order it online.

04:13.545 --> 04:16.048
Or whatever. It's fine.
You can come back and pay for it later.

04:17.716 --> 04:19.593
- Thank you. I--
- Yeah.

04:19.593 --> 04:21.803
- I promise I'll be back with the money.
- Yeah.

04:23.597 --> 04:24.598
Thank you.

04:25.098 --> 04:25.974
- Bye.
- See ya.

04:35.150 --> 04:36.360
You probably have a boyfriend.

04:39.238 --> 04:41.156
Idiot. "Probably have a boyfriend."

04:50.582 --> 04:51.959
- Hi. Remember me?
- Hey.

04:51.959 --> 04:53.210
Yeah.

04:53.794 --> 04:54.711
Got your money.

04:54.711 --> 04:56.630
You didn't have to do that today.

04:56.630 --> 04:58.215
I didn't wanna leave you hanging.

05:00.259 --> 05:01.176
Thank you.

05:02.344 --> 05:03.554
Just keep the change.

05:04.513 --> 05:06.223
Okay. Thanks.

05:06.723 --> 05:09.059
Okay. Well. See ya.

05:10.269 --> 05:11.854
- All right. Yeah.
- Yeah.

05:11.854 --> 05:13.272
- Have a good one.
- You too.

05:21.405 --> 05:22.406
- Hey.
- Hello.

05:23.574 --> 05:26.118
So, remember this morning
when you asked me out to dinner?

05:26.118 --> 05:28.620
- Oh, yeah. I'm sorry. I didn't mean to--
- No, no, no.

05:28.620 --> 05:31.582
I-- I actually wanted to say yes.

05:32.332 --> 05:33.667
I was standing there

05:33.667 --> 05:35.460
thinking how nice it would be
if this guy asked me out,

05:35.460 --> 05:37.421
and right as I thought it, you did.
And I--

05:37.921 --> 05:40.048
I don't know. I panicked.

05:40.716 --> 05:41.884
You panicked?

05:41.884 --> 05:43.343
I panicked.

05:45.053 --> 05:46.221
I'm Sandra.

05:47.139 --> 05:48.390
Tom.

05:48.891 --> 05:50.100
Nice to meet you, Tom.

05:52.102 --> 05:53.103
Nice to meet you.

05:54.438 --> 05:57.191
- So, Mott Street?
- Yeah. If that-- Yeah.

05:58.192 --> 06:00.068
- Okay. Yeah. Okay.
- This way.

06:01.486 --> 06:03.155
- You-- After you. Yeah.
- All right.

06:03.155 --> 06:04.865
I have my bag.

06:04.865 --> 06:07.743
No, I do too. It's getting kind of cold.

06:08.619 --> 06:09.620
- That--
- Sorry...

06:09.620 --> 06:10.829
- Backpack buddies.
- Buddies.

06:10.829 --> 06:14.082
Yeah, and, like,
what have I gotten myself into?

06:14.082 --> 06:16.376
You know?
Like, a short story is one thing.

06:16.376 --> 06:19.922
- A novel, that's, like, 300 pages and--
- I know. And sometimes more.

06:19.922 --> 06:22.633
Exactly. And, you know, here they are
offering me real money, you know?

06:22.633 --> 06:24.009
I have to deliver something.

06:24.009 --> 06:28.055
- So, what'd you do?
- I had a year-long panic attack, and I--

06:28.055 --> 06:29.806
I wrote this book that was terrible.

06:29.806 --> 06:31.683
Come on. I'm sure it wasn't that bad.

06:31.683 --> 06:34.186
No, no, it was bad. It was-- It was awful.
They wouldn't publish it.

06:35.062 --> 06:36.188
Ouch.

06:36.188 --> 06:37.272
- Yeah.
- Sorry.

06:37.272 --> 06:39.816
No, it's fine. You know,
at least I got to keep the advance.

06:41.360 --> 06:42.611
Do you still write?

06:42.611 --> 06:44.530
No. Not really.

06:45.364 --> 06:47.866
You know, all this happened
around the time that my mom died, and--

06:49.826 --> 06:50.661
I don't know, I--

06:50.661 --> 06:54.748
Things got dark for me,
and I kinda just gave up.

06:57.417 --> 06:59.086
My parents died when I was a kid.

07:01.505 --> 07:02.589
I'm sorry to hear that.

07:04.383 --> 07:05.384
Must've been tough.

07:08.554 --> 07:10.514
Anyway, yeah.

07:11.390 --> 07:12.766
I started managing the bookstore.

07:13.267 --> 07:15.978
That kinda pulled me out
of my depression, or whatever.

07:15.978 --> 07:18.939
And, yeah, it takes up most of my time.

07:18.939 --> 07:20.983
Must be nice being surrounded
by books all day.

07:22.401 --> 07:23.402
It's the best.

07:26.655 --> 07:28.156
After my parents passed,

07:28.156 --> 07:31.827
my brother and I hopped
from one foster family to the next.

07:32.744 --> 07:34.246
One point,
we were staying with this couple

07:34.246 --> 07:36.456
that had this great collection of novels.

07:37.457 --> 07:41.336
And one night, I started reading
<i>Jane Eyre,</i> and here was this character

07:41.336 --> 07:43.589
that was, sort of, going through
everything I was going through.

07:43.589 --> 07:46.550
And I didn't want it to end.

07:47.384 --> 07:50.929
I finished it, went back to page one
and started reading it all over again.

07:53.015 --> 07:54.600
Just loved books ever since.

07:56.226 --> 07:57.227
<i>Jane Eyre,</i> huh?

07:58.896 --> 07:59.897
<i>Jane Eyre.</i>

08:02.941 --> 08:04.026
Can I show you something?

08:52.115 --> 08:53.158
Oh, my God.

08:54.618 --> 08:56.036
Is this a first edition?

08:59.039 --> 09:00.123
Is this real?

09:02.584 --> 09:03.585
This is real.

09:08.090 --> 09:09.424
How can I be sure?

09:29.278 --> 09:31.822
<i>I mean, some of these professors
are so obnoxious.</i>

09:31.822 --> 09:35.951
Actually used the phrase
"the vaginization of German literature."

09:35.951 --> 09:37.411
- The what?
- I mean, I'm pretty sure

09:37.411 --> 09:39.538
"vaginization" isn't even a real word.

09:41.373 --> 09:42.791
Where'd you learn how to cook?

09:42.791 --> 09:44.626
I spent my junior year in Florence.

09:45.210 --> 09:46.461
<i>Do you speak Italian?</i>

09:46.962 --> 09:48.589
<i>I used to speak it well,</i>

09:48.589 --> 09:51.633
- now it's a bit rusty, unfortunately.

09:51.633 --> 09:53.051
- Hello!
- <i>Did you like Italy?</i>

09:55.137 --> 09:56.555
<i>I have great memories.</i>

09:56.555 --> 09:57.931
This is amazing!

09:57.931 --> 10:01.268
But, I had this boyfriend
who was a real jerk.

10:06.732 --> 10:09.318
And what about you?
Where did you learn to speak Italian?

10:09.318 --> 10:11.528
My mom was from Italy.

10:12.029 --> 10:14.823
- And I watch a lot of Fellini movies.
- <i>I love Fellini.</i>

10:15.949 --> 10:18.202
<i>Have you ever had your heart broken?</i>

10:20.829 --> 10:21.872
<i>Yeah, once or twice.</i>

10:46.396 --> 10:47.648
I really like you.

10:55.280 --> 10:56.281
Okay.

11:02.496 --> 11:03.705
I really like you too.

11:08.585 --> 11:09.586
Okay.

11:12.673 --> 11:14.174
- Just hear me out.
- No, just-- No, I can't.

11:14.174 --> 11:16.343
- I need your help.
- I'm not doing this.

11:16.343 --> 11:18.011
- What do you mean you're not doing this?
- I can't.

11:18.011 --> 11:20.013
It's me and you.
It's me and you against the world,

11:20.013 --> 11:21.682
- do you remember that?
- Can you please just go?

11:21.682 --> 11:23.934
- It's me and you against the world.
- Jason, I need you to stop.

11:23.934 --> 11:26.854
Please, I need you. Don't walk out
on me. You are the last thing that I have

11:26.854 --> 11:28.355
- on this earth. You are the last person--
- Jason!

11:28.355 --> 11:30.691
- Sandra!
- Jason, please don't.

11:31.608 --> 11:32.484
Sandra!

11:32.484 --> 11:33.944
- Just go. Just go.
- Please.

11:33.944 --> 11:36.947
Please open the door.
Sandra, Sandra, open the door.

11:38.031 --> 11:40.534
Fuck! Fuck!

11:42.035 --> 11:43.161
Fucking bitch.

11:46.206 --> 11:47.124
Are you okay?

11:50.002 --> 11:51.003
Who was that?

11:53.922 --> 11:55.465
It's my brother. He needs money.

11:59.219 --> 12:00.596
Jason wasn't so lucky.

12:02.347 --> 12:03.932
Some of the homes he was put in were...

12:06.310 --> 12:07.686
a nightmare.

12:08.604 --> 12:09.897
It's not your fault.

12:12.482 --> 12:15.777
I know, but he's the only family I got.

12:18.447 --> 12:21.241
"All happy families are alike."
And all that.

12:24.995 --> 12:28.165
No matter how many times
he screws me over, I can't not help him.

12:29.166 --> 12:32.127
He's my brother. I love him.

12:32.127 --> 12:34.922
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

12:35.506 --> 12:40.511
<i>Happy birthday, dear Tom</i>

12:41.220 --> 12:45.849
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

12:45.849 --> 12:48.352
Yay. Okay, you gotta blow. Blow here.

12:49.728 --> 12:51.146
You gotta blow harder. Come on.

12:51.146 --> 12:52.564
Harder. Come on.

12:52.564 --> 12:55.484
Yes! Yes! Yes! We got it. We got it.

12:56.276 --> 12:57.611
<i>So, how long have you known Tom?</i>

12:57.611 --> 12:59.696
Just a few weeks.

13:00.739 --> 13:04.952
- Seems like so much longer.
- Yeah, I know. It's been kind of intense.

13:04.952 --> 13:08.121
She's like a sexy librarian or something.

13:09.540 --> 13:14.878
- She's-- She's literally your dream girl.
- I know. She's just incredible.

13:14.878 --> 13:16.964
- Where did you go to undergrad?
- Vassar.

13:17.881 --> 13:19.550
Oh, my God. So did I.

13:20.467 --> 13:22.928
You know, I thought you looked familiar.
When did you graduate?

13:22.928 --> 13:24.012
Class of '14.

13:24.012 --> 13:25.097
Class of '16.

13:25.597 --> 13:27.015
Did you hang out at the Mug a lot?

13:27.808 --> 13:30.769
Honestly, I spent most of my time
at the library.

13:32.020 --> 13:35.691
But don't tell Tom. I'm trying to maintain
the illusion I'm not a total nerd.

13:35.691 --> 13:37.776
Glad to see that you're doing okay.

13:38.610 --> 13:40.863
You were in a bad place there, so...

13:40.863 --> 13:42.197
I was just a little depressed.

13:45.868 --> 13:48.328
Okay. It got bad but, you know, it's like,

13:48.328 --> 13:50.956
who hasn't been borderline suicidal
at some point in their life?

13:51.707 --> 13:53.792
It's not funny.
Not supposed to joke about that stuff.

13:53.792 --> 13:57.087
- Come on. Come on.
- Okay, you're right.

13:57.087 --> 14:00.132
But I'm good now.

14:00.132 --> 14:04.011
You know, like, I'm great, actually.

14:06.680 --> 14:10.976
It was pretty great.
Yeah, we actually met in the bookstore.

14:16.064 --> 14:17.232
Hi.

14:22.863 --> 14:24.948
How come we always come back to my place?

14:27.075 --> 14:28.076
What do you mean?

14:30.162 --> 14:31.997
I wanna see where you live.

14:32.581 --> 14:36.084
It's-- It's kind of uncomfortable there.

14:39.171 --> 14:42.382
Well, my place
isn't exactly the Four Seasons.

14:42.382 --> 14:44.176
No, it's not that. It's...

14:46.178 --> 14:48.805
I live with my dad and his new wife, and...

14:50.682 --> 14:52.518
My dad and I don't really get along.

14:57.814 --> 14:59.858
He thinks I'm a disappointment.

15:01.568 --> 15:03.153
"All happy families are alike."

15:04.530 --> 15:05.656
And all that, right?

15:09.493 --> 15:12.371
Anyways, he's really sick, so...

15:15.290 --> 15:16.333
Sorry he's sick.

15:18.252 --> 15:19.253
It's okay.

15:22.047 --> 15:23.757
But you're not a disappointment.

15:52.369 --> 15:53.495
Sandra?

16:02.754 --> 16:03.672
Hey.

16:04.256 --> 16:05.174
Are you okay?

16:05.674 --> 16:09.344
You're not--
You're not returning my texts.

16:11.638 --> 16:12.639
I'm sorry.

16:14.683 --> 16:17.477
My brother's in trouble.
He owes them money,

16:17.477 --> 16:20.063
so they cracked three of his ribs,
broke his cheekbone.

16:20.814 --> 16:23.233
Said if he didn't pay up,
they'd come back and finish the job.

16:23.233 --> 16:24.401
How much does he owe them?

16:24.401 --> 16:26.069
Paying them back is not an option.

16:26.069 --> 16:28.488
- So, what is an option?
- I give him money, and he runs.

16:28.488 --> 16:32.659
Okay. So, say he runs,
and they can't find him.

16:32.659 --> 16:34.912
Who do you think
they're gonna come looking for to collect?

16:34.912 --> 16:37.623
Me? No, they don't even know I exist.

16:37.623 --> 16:39.708
- Are you sure?
- I'm not sure of anything.

16:42.878 --> 16:45.547
- You have to pay them off.
- I told you that's not possible.

16:45.547 --> 16:48.175
- How much do they want?
- $350,000.

16:49.092 --> 16:50.677
And they want it in four days,

16:50.677 --> 16:52.721
so short of robbing a bank,
that's just not gonna happen.

16:54.348 --> 16:55.432
I can give you the money.

16:58.185 --> 16:59.520
- What?
- It's in the bank.

16:59.520 --> 17:00.646
I can just go make a withdrawal.

17:00.646 --> 17:02.940
You wouldn't have to rob it.

17:03.649 --> 17:06.108
I don't understand. You live at home.

17:06.108 --> 17:09.029
- You work in a bookstore.
- No, I own a bookstore.

17:09.530 --> 17:12.324
How do you think I manage to keep it open?
All that place does is lose money.

17:12.324 --> 17:14.867
You're saying you have that money
just sitting in a bank?

17:15.452 --> 17:18.079
Yeah. More. Yeah. My father has money.

17:20.665 --> 17:22.209
Why is this
the first time I'm hearing about this?

17:22.209 --> 17:23.961
Why does that matter?
Maybe I didn't want you to know.

17:23.961 --> 17:25.253
Well, honestly, it's kinda fucked up

17:25.253 --> 17:26.922
- that you didn't say anything.
- Are you kidding me?

17:26.922 --> 17:28.841
- I'm telling you that I can help you.
- I can't take your money.

17:28.841 --> 17:31.635
- Why not?
- Because it's $350,000. That's why.

17:33.470 --> 17:35.305
I appreciate the offer. I really do.

17:35.305 --> 17:37.474
But let's face it,
we're practically strangers.

17:42.896 --> 17:45.774
First of all, it's not my money,
it's my father's money.

17:45.774 --> 17:48.402
And it's not like he earned it
in some noble way.

17:48.402 --> 17:49.653
He has a hedge fund.

17:50.320 --> 17:55.409
And second of all,
fuck you for saying we're strangers.

17:58.704 --> 18:00.372
You are the best thing
that's ever happened to me.

18:05.752 --> 18:08.005
<i>I'm going to pay you back,
no matter how long it takes.</i>

18:08.005 --> 18:10.382
<i>That's okay. I wish
you'd let me come with you though.</i>

18:10.382 --> 18:12.843
<i>I told you I don't want you
anywhere near these people.</i>

18:12.843 --> 18:14.136
- It's all there.
- Got it.

18:14.803 --> 18:17.306
<i>I'll be fine. What are you doing tonight?</i>

18:18.473 --> 18:21.476
I'm-- I was hoping to hang out
with this pretty girl that I know.

18:22.186 --> 18:25.397
Well, there's this great
little Japanese restaurant on Mott Street.

18:25.898 --> 18:27.608
If you're not doing anything,
dinner's on me.

18:31.195 --> 18:32.196
Hey.

18:39.494 --> 18:40.370
I love you.

18:41.121 --> 18:42.748
I'm so sorry about all this.

18:53.008 --> 18:54.009
All right.

19:38.262 --> 19:39.263
Sandra?

19:41.723 --> 19:43.392
Sandra, are you okay?

19:45.978 --> 19:49.231
Sandra! Sandra!

19:54.528 --> 19:55.529
Sandra!

19:58.949 --> 19:59.950
Sandra!

20:41.491 --> 20:42.576
Shit.

20:57.424 --> 21:00.427
How's Christmas Day? It's not that bad.

21:02.221 --> 21:03.472
Hey, you Larusso?

21:05.974 --> 21:07.017
Over here.

21:11.480 --> 21:13.398
- You're pretty late, Sandy.
- I'm sorry.

21:13.398 --> 21:15.567
There's no cabs.
It's fucking Christmas Eve.

21:16.652 --> 21:17.736
Where's Carl?

21:18.320 --> 21:20.781
Mr. Knutson's wife is sick.
I'll be taking over for him.

21:20.781 --> 21:22.324
Carl usually--

21:22.991 --> 21:25.953
Mr. Knutson usually has us meet
in his office.

21:25.953 --> 21:28.372
Yeah, I thought we'd meet somewhere
a little less formal given the holiday.

21:29.122 --> 21:30.791
But if you'd rather go to my office,
we can do that.

21:30.791 --> 21:32.000
No, it's fine.

21:32.000 --> 21:33.085
Great. Have a seat.

21:37.923 --> 21:39.842
- So, where were you tonight?
- Nowhere.

21:42.553 --> 21:44.054
Just with a friend. Girl I work with.

21:44.054 --> 21:45.806
- A girl you work with at Starbucks?
- Yeah.

21:45.806 --> 21:48.559
Caroline.
I can give you her number if you want.

21:48.559 --> 21:49.810
That won't be necessary.

21:49.810 --> 21:51.520
- Did you do any drugs tonight, Sandy?
- No.

21:51.520 --> 21:53.981
Did you engage in any behavior
that would violate your parole?

21:53.981 --> 21:55.482
Nope. No.

21:56.066 --> 21:57.943
How is that job? You doing good?

21:57.943 --> 21:59.945
Yeah. It's fine.

21:59.945 --> 22:03.657
Yeah. Starbucks is great.
There's lots of opportunity there.

22:04.241 --> 22:05.659
Yeah, I love it.

22:06.577 --> 22:07.870
Yeah.

22:07.870 --> 22:08.829
The thing is, Sandy,

22:08.829 --> 22:11.373
I went to your job and they told me
you haven't been there in a month.

22:14.835 --> 22:16.336
Yeah. I can explain.

22:18.297 --> 22:20.591
- I got into a fight with the manager...
- Yeah.

22:20.591 --> 22:23.218
...'cause he's a real--
he's a real fucking perv, okay?

22:23.218 --> 22:24.803
And I've been looking
for another job, so--

22:24.803 --> 22:26.430
Having a job is
a part of your parole agreement.

22:26.430 --> 22:27.806
- Do you understand?
- Uh-huh, yeah.

22:27.806 --> 22:29.224
So, you getting fired is strike one.

22:29.224 --> 22:30.851
So, let me ask you a question.

22:30.851 --> 22:32.895
If I give you a drug test right now,
