It's just that I can't
go through that again,

49:12.828 --> 49:15.455
- and that can't happen here.
- Mom, I'm clean.

49:15.455 --> 49:16.832
My God. What the fuck is--

49:16.832 --> 49:19.251
What do you want?
You want me to prove it to you?

49:19.251 --> 49:20.377
A fucking piss test?

49:20.377 --> 49:23.005
- Is that what you want?
- Stop. What? What are you doing?

49:23.005 --> 49:26.133
- Here. I'll do it right now! Okay?
- No! No, don't. Stop! Stop!

49:26.133 --> 49:28.635
- You can see for yourself!
- Don't do that. Stop it right now!

49:33.390 --> 49:34.433
Prove it to you.

49:40.022 --> 49:40.939
Go ahead.

49:42.357 --> 49:44.985
- Test it.
- Please don't do this to me.

49:44.985 --> 49:46.069
Test it!

49:47.321 --> 49:51.325
Please. Please. Please.
Please, don't do this to me.

50:02.628 --> 50:03.962
Mom, I'm sorry.

50:09.092 --> 50:10.469
I'm sorry, Mom.

50:10.469 --> 50:14.765
Why do you do this?
Why do you do this to me?

50:15.474 --> 50:17.267
I'm really sorry.

50:19.853 --> 50:23.941
Just-- I still need a place to stay, okay?

50:26.735 --> 50:27.778
Please?

50:27.778 --> 50:30.364
You can stay.
Just not for very long, okay?

50:33.784 --> 50:36.161
Thank you. I love you.

50:38.956 --> 50:39.873
Thank you.

50:50.509 --> 50:51.593
You enjoy the show?

51:07.067 --> 51:09.486
I'm so-- I'm so sorry.

51:09.486 --> 51:12.781
I'm-- I'm so-- I'm so sorry. I'm sorry.

51:29.548 --> 51:32.134
He spent the last year
putting together a company

51:32.134 --> 51:34.803
to charter boats in the Bahamas,

51:34.803 --> 51:39.266
but then the hurricane wiped that out,
which is too bad because he was so happy.

51:39.266 --> 51:42.186
- He was doing so well--
- Madeline. How does he live?

51:42.186 --> 51:44.313
Well, his father left him some money,
and--

51:46.690 --> 51:48.192
I help him out from time to time.

51:49.860 --> 51:50.861
Of course you do.

51:51.737 --> 51:54.406
I was so young when he was born, you know?

51:54.406 --> 51:58.160
And then his father died,
and I'm suddenly a widow,

51:58.160 --> 52:01.371
and I didn't always know
how to be a mother.

52:01.371 --> 52:04.041
It's up to him to do better.
He-He's an adult.

52:04.041 --> 52:05.959
No, he isn't. And that's my fault.

52:07.044 --> 52:09.880
He's always been my little Max.
And he can't swim without me.

52:11.131 --> 52:12.132
Morning, Mom.

52:13.550 --> 52:16.637
Hi, sweetheart. How'd you sleep?

52:17.721 --> 52:20.974
Great. Room's got an amazing view.

52:22.643 --> 52:23.644
Good.

52:24.811 --> 52:28.148
Well, I--
I actually have an appointment downtown,

52:28.148 --> 52:31.902
but I was thinking if you were free
that maybe we could have lunch together.

52:33.070 --> 52:34.988
At one o'clock. Via Carota?

52:35.656 --> 52:37.783
- Sounds great.
- Okay. Perfect.

52:40.035 --> 52:40.953
See you later.

52:47.960 --> 52:48.961
Bye, honey.

53:01.640 --> 53:02.558
Richard?

53:06.562 --> 53:08.146
I'm sorry about yesterday.

53:08.146 --> 53:12.693
I took a Klonopin,
and I had a lot of drinks.

53:13.944 --> 53:16.989
Max, we're gonna be in each other's lives

53:16.989 --> 53:18.657
for the foreseeable future.

53:19.366 --> 53:21.201
Let's make the best of it, shall we?

53:22.536 --> 53:25.539
You know, your mother and I are attending

53:25.539 --> 53:29.459
a benefit tonight
for the Richard Hobbes Foundation.

53:30.294 --> 53:31.879
My late wife founded it.

53:31.879 --> 53:35.507
We make all sorts
of charitable contributions.

53:36.925 --> 53:38.844
Did you want me to make a donation?

53:38.844 --> 53:40.804
Because, honestly,
I'm a little light right now.

53:40.804 --> 53:44.141
No. No, I figured you might wanna join us.

53:44.933 --> 53:48.979
There's a gonna be a--
a few very hip musical acts.

53:48.979 --> 53:51.231
They tell me they're quite relevant.

53:54.443 --> 53:56.320
<i>There's gonna be
a lot of young people your age.</i>

53:57.946 --> 53:58.947
<i>Lot of young women.</i>

54:00.949 --> 54:04.912
Thank you, but I think
I should just stay in and rest.

54:07.372 --> 54:09.875
Yeah. Fair enough.

54:32.814 --> 54:35.943
Well, you were terrible.
You treated him like a waiter.

54:35.943 --> 54:38.946
I still have no idea who he is.

54:38.946 --> 54:43.408
No, he's-- he's on that TV show.
He plays a spy. He's very famous.

54:43.992 --> 54:46.787
All night, all I could think about
was being alone with you.

54:46.787 --> 54:48.038
You're alone with me now.

54:54.169 --> 54:57.798
I don't care about actors.
You should know that.

55:00.175 --> 55:02.261
I just want you all to myself.

55:08.141 --> 55:09.560
- Sir, calm down.
- I asked you to identify...

55:09.560 --> 55:11.144
Sir, the police are here.

55:12.020 --> 55:15.440
- Police? Hey! What's going on here?
- Fuck does that even fucking mean?

55:15.440 --> 55:17.651
- Sir, excuse me. I'm NYPD.
- Oh, my G--

55:17.651 --> 55:19.528
Detective Collins.
Does this young man live here?

55:19.528 --> 55:21.572
- Well, he's staying here.
- I don't fucking live here.

55:21.572 --> 55:24.491
- What did you do?
- Nothing. I didn't do anything.

55:24.491 --> 55:25.993
He solicited drugs
from an undercover officer.

55:25.993 --> 55:28.203
You came up to me
and tried to sell me fucking cocaine.

55:28.203 --> 55:29.913
- And you said yes.
- Don't put words in my mouth.

55:29.913 --> 55:32.082
- Detective, how bad is this?
- It's not looking good.

55:32.958 --> 55:33.876
He has a few offenses.

55:33.876 --> 55:36.295
We ran his name,
and he's looking at doing some time.

55:36.295 --> 55:37.963
- Oh, my God. Max.
- Wha-- What happens now?

55:37.963 --> 55:40.549
- I'll take him downtown--
- Fuck that, dude. I'm outta here.

55:40.549 --> 55:41.884
Get your fucking hands off of me!

55:41.884 --> 55:44.678
Richard!
Richard, please. Stop him. Stop him!

55:44.678 --> 55:45.846
Calm down!

55:45.846 --> 55:48.682
- Fuck!
- Detective, can we talk about this?

55:50.517 --> 55:51.810
- Fuck.
- Now?

55:58.025 --> 56:01.028
I make large donations
to the NYPD every year.

56:01.028 --> 56:02.404
Yes, sir, I'm aware of that.

56:02.404 --> 56:04.740
That's the reason for the courtesy call.
It's why I'm here.

56:04.740 --> 56:06.867
I know the commissioner.
Marty is a good friend.

56:06.867 --> 56:10.037
- I can put in a good word for you.
- Richard, you don't have to do that.

56:10.037 --> 56:12.247
My word carries weight in this city.

56:15.250 --> 56:16.668
That can cut both ways.

56:16.668 --> 56:19.755
I really appreciate what you've done,
coming here.

56:19.755 --> 56:20.881
I don't know, sir.

56:20.881 --> 56:22.382
I'm gonna pay you for your time.

56:23.383 --> 56:25.802
I-- I can't do that. No, I'm-- I'm sorry.

56:26.345 --> 56:28.180
Take the fucking money, Detective.

56:33.644 --> 56:36.063
- Stop. He's not a cop.
- What?

56:36.063 --> 56:37.523
- Ma'am, ex--
- Shut up.

56:39.566 --> 56:41.777
This is-- This is what Max does.

56:41.777 --> 56:44.404
He plays these--
these little confidence games.

56:45.697 --> 56:49.201
That's what this is, isn't it? This is--
This is one of your games, right?

56:50.160 --> 56:51.912
- I can assure you that I'm--
- You get out.

56:51.912 --> 56:55.123
Get out or I really will call the police.
I mean it. Get out of here.

57:02.881 --> 57:04.258
Tipsy, I mean, I think--

57:04.258 --> 57:05.926
- Dude, fuck.
- You better-- You better go.

57:05.926 --> 57:07.928
- Do you think this is funny?
- Why'd you fucking break?

57:07.928 --> 57:09.346
Do you think this is funny?

57:09.346 --> 57:10.639
Come on, man.

57:11.431 --> 57:13.267
- You okay?
- Get out of here. Get out of here.

57:13.267 --> 57:15.102
- Okay.
- Sorry. I'm sorry.

57:15.102 --> 57:17.104
- I'll call you later. Thank you.
- All right, dude.

57:17.855 --> 57:19.022
Hope I catch you later, bro.

57:19.857 --> 57:21.024
Oh, my God.

57:21.024 --> 57:22.401
Mom, listen.

57:24.611 --> 57:25.904
I gave you everything, you know.

57:25.904 --> 57:28.448
You-- You had every advantage.

57:28.949 --> 57:31.118
You-- You didn't--
You didn't want for anything,

57:31.118 --> 57:32.786
and this is what you do to me?

57:33.370 --> 57:35.581
- You humiliate me in front of him?
- It's just a little--

57:43.714 --> 57:44.798
I want you to leave.

57:48.802 --> 57:50.345
I don't want you here anymore.

58:01.899 --> 58:07.321
All that work for $1,000.

58:07.946 --> 58:10.032
Let me give you a piece of advice, Max.

58:11.200 --> 58:14.244
If you're gonna steal, steal a lot.

58:44.358 --> 58:45.526
I'm sorry I hit you.

58:47.069 --> 58:48.070
Forget it.

58:48.654 --> 58:50.739
No, I took it too far.

58:53.367 --> 58:54.368
Let me see.

59:09.758 --> 59:11.260
Is it too early for a drink?

59:21.478 --> 59:23.188
I don't like the way you look at him.

59:23.188 --> 59:24.314
Come on.

59:28.026 --> 59:29.069
You like him a little bit.

59:29.653 --> 59:31.697
Of course I like him. He's a billionaire.

59:33.073 --> 59:34.491
That's not what I'm talking about.

59:35.492 --> 59:37.828
Look, I feel really good about this.

59:37.828 --> 59:39.371
We're very close.

59:40.330 --> 59:42.791
He wants to meet with you
at his office at one o'clock.

59:49.047 --> 59:52.342
Well, maybe I don't wanna do this anymore.

59:52.342 --> 59:55.053
Why not? Don't be jealous.

59:58.765 --> 1:00:00.475
You know I don't like old men.

1:00:04.605 --> 1:00:05.981
You know what I like.

1:00:13.906 --> 1:00:14.990
Okay.

1:00:17.868 --> 1:00:18.702
No.

1:00:22.623 --> 1:00:23.665
Tell me what I like.

1:00:28.837 --> 1:00:29.880
You like me.

1:00:33.592 --> 1:00:34.593
I like you.

1:00:41.016 --> 1:00:42.267
Why do I like you?

1:00:44.144 --> 1:00:46.355
Because I get you what you want.

1:00:52.611 --> 1:00:53.904
So, get me what I want.

1:00:56.949 --> 1:00:58.283
Get me what I want.

1:00:58.825 --> 1:00:59.910
Okay.

1:01:42.244 --> 1:01:43.954
Max, thanks for coming.

1:01:44.705 --> 1:01:48.000
Hey. Are you okay?

1:01:48.000 --> 1:01:51.211
Yeah, it's just maintenance.
Here, follow me.

1:01:51.712 --> 1:01:54.631
I wanted to apologize about last night.

1:01:54.631 --> 1:01:55.966
It was inappropriate.

1:01:57.050 --> 1:01:58.719
That's a hell of an understatement.

1:01:59.928 --> 1:02:02.639
You know,
when your mother first told me about you,

1:02:03.182 --> 1:02:07.311
she said that you were well-educated,
smart, clever.

1:02:07.895 --> 1:02:12.482
I thought, you know, I'm always
on the lookout for a young man like that.

1:02:12.482 --> 1:02:15.360
- Are you offering me a job here?
- No. I doubt if you'd want one.

1:02:17.738 --> 1:02:19.156
What are you doing here?

1:02:19.740 --> 1:02:21.366
Did you schedule a meeting?

1:02:21.366 --> 1:02:23.160
No. I didn't know that I needed one.

1:02:23.160 --> 1:02:24.244
What is it, Tom?

1:02:25.704 --> 1:02:26.538
I'm back.

1:02:26.538 --> 1:02:29.374
Yeah, I can see that. So, what is it?

1:02:30.125 --> 1:02:31.877
Just wanted to say hi,
see how you're feeling...

1:02:31.877 --> 1:02:34.755
- Now is not a good time.
- All right, cool. See you around, Dad.

1:02:36.590 --> 1:02:37.591
Tom.

1:02:42.721 --> 1:02:43.722
Come on, in here.

1:02:44.890 --> 1:02:45.974
That was my son.

1:02:46.517 --> 1:02:49.311
I always assumed
he would inherit all this.

1:02:50.521 --> 1:02:53.315
Then his mother died
and he didn't take it well.

1:02:53.941 --> 1:02:56.735
He doesn't have the fortitude
to work here. He's weak.

1:02:59.321 --> 1:03:04.785
When he turned 21,
I offered him anything he wanted.

1:03:05.911 --> 1:03:08.497
You know what my son asked for?

1:03:09.790 --> 1:03:10.832
I don't know, Richard.

1:03:11.333 --> 1:03:16.129
A signed copy of Charlotte Brontë's
<i>Jane Eyre.</i>

1:03:16.964 --> 1:03:19.132
Now he wants to open a bookstore.

1:03:20.092 --> 1:03:21.802
Not exactly a sound investment.

1:03:22.678 --> 1:03:25.222
No. But I'm gonna give it to him anyway.

1:03:27.307 --> 1:03:28.475
You know why, Max?

1:03:30.644 --> 1:03:32.271
Because we only get one life.

1:03:32.271 --> 1:03:37.025
And I will not be my son's jailer
for his brief time on earth.

1:03:43.282 --> 1:03:45.659
I want you to be honest with yourself, Max.

1:03:47.160 --> 1:03:51.415
If I were to hire you to work for me,
how do you think it would end?

1:03:52.916 --> 1:03:54.042
Not well.

1:03:55.085 --> 1:03:56.128
I agree.

1:03:58.297 --> 1:04:03.594
Still, I want to offer you a job.
I'm thinking $60,000 a month.

1:04:03.594 --> 1:04:06.221
Sixty grand a month? For what?

1:04:06.722 --> 1:04:11.185
To go out and find opportunity.
Make a mark for yourself.

1:04:12.019 --> 1:04:13.228
You want me gone.

1:04:14.396 --> 1:04:19.568
You cause your mother anguish, Max.
And I will not have it.

1:04:21.361 --> 1:04:23.280
So, what am I then? A bad investment?

1:04:23.280 --> 1:04:25.365
I didn't get where I am
making bad investments.

1:04:25.365 --> 1:04:29.244
Is that what I'm worth, Richard?
Sixty thousand dollars a month?

1:04:29.244 --> 1:04:31.580
I'm offering you an opportunity.

1:04:34.041 --> 1:04:35.709
I want a year's salary up-front.

1:04:37.044 --> 1:04:39.838
That can be arranged.
I'll just transfer the money in--

1:04:39.838 --> 1:04:42.633
Transfer the money?
No. What? So I can pay taxes?

1:04:42.633 --> 1:04:43.926
Hire an accountant? No.

1:04:45.135 --> 1:04:46.678
I want cash up-front.

1:04:50.933 --> 1:04:54.061
Get me the cash
and you get my mom all to yourself.

1:04:54.061 --> 1:04:57.606
I'll be gone. You won't even hear from me.
Not even a fucking postcard.

1:05:02.694 --> 1:05:03.779
Wait here.

1:06:57.518 --> 1:07:00.687
- We did it.
- We did it, baby.

1:07:06.193 --> 1:07:07.653
Where the fuck is my money?

1:07:10.906 --> 1:07:11.865
Y'all look good.

1:07:17.704 --> 1:07:18.789
Let's go.

1:07:23.627 --> 1:07:26.588
- Yeah!
- Let's do it.

1:07:28.215 --> 1:07:29.216
Here we go.

1:07:29.842 --> 1:07:31.426
We got the big Gs, buddy.

1:07:32.761 --> 1:07:35.055
Yo, wait, look.

1:07:35.055 --> 1:07:37.558
There is this new guy named Goldie.

1:07:37.558 --> 1:07:39.226
- He from, like, LA.
- Yeah.

1:07:39.226 --> 1:07:41.603
He started out working as a stuntman
before he was grifting,

1:07:41.603 --> 1:07:42.855
or whatever the fuck we doing.

1:07:42.855 --> 1:07:45.023
He started working as a stuntman. Crazy.

1:07:45.023 --> 1:07:47.401
He comes highly recommended
and he's looking for a score.

1:07:47.401 --> 1:07:48.485
And I need y'all.

1:07:49.570 --> 1:07:50.487
Tipsy...

1:07:53.156 --> 1:07:54.157
We're out.

1:07:55.242 --> 1:07:57.452
Come on, man.
What you-- What, y'all retiring?

1:07:57.452 --> 1:07:59.663
- No. No, no, no. No.
- That's it?

1:07:59.663 --> 1:08:01.456
What y'all gonna do?
Do the whole-- Come on.

1:08:01.456 --> 1:08:02.583
No, we're taking--

1:08:02.583 --> 1:08:05.502
- We're just gonna take a vacation.
- We're-- We're-- Yeah.

1:08:05.502 --> 1:08:07.671
- Taking a vacation.
- Okay. Well, y'all let me know

1:08:07.671 --> 1:08:09.590
- whenever y'all get back. Okay?
- Okay.

1:08:09.590 --> 1:08:11.049
Y'all gonna wanna meet him.

1:08:11.049 --> 1:08:12.134
Big shit, all right?

1:08:17.598 --> 1:08:18.599
Hey.

1:08:19.892 --> 1:08:21.560
You're bullshitting me. Where my money at?

1:08:26.857 --> 1:08:27.733
Come on.

1:08:27.733 --> 1:08:28.649
What?

1:08:30.694 --> 1:08:34.406
- That's it. Tipsy, that's it.
- No.

1:08:35.698 --> 1:08:37.158
We had expenses...

1:08:37.158 --> 1:08:39.661
- We handled some expenses.
- ...that we didn't account for.

1:08:39.661 --> 1:08:43.665
Yeah, okay, but this-- No. No, no.
This isn't what we agreed on, man.

1:08:43.665 --> 1:08:46.376
- I know, but things change.
- Yeah.

1:08:50.005 --> 1:08:53.091
This is becoming a habit with y'all two.
I'm starting to feel like I'm the mark.

1:08:53.716 --> 1:08:55.886
- Now we're laughing about it.
- No. Come on, man. No.

1:08:55.886 --> 1:08:56.803
- No, no, no.
- Uh-uh.

1:08:56.803 --> 1:08:57.888
Absolutely not.

1:09:02.935 --> 1:09:04.728
It was a beautiful con though, right?

1:09:04.728 --> 1:09:06.854
You can thank Madeline--
Madeline for that.

1:09:07.481 --> 1:09:08.857
Stop it. Stop it.

1:09:09.358 --> 1:09:11.276
Thank you, Madeline.

1:09:11.276 --> 1:09:13.278
You're welcome, Tipsy. You're welcome.

1:09:13.278 --> 1:09:15.738
- Thank you, Tipsy.
- Yeah. Thank you for everything, man.

1:09:15.738 --> 1:09:18.158
- I'll ca-- I'll call you.
- Yeah. For sure.

1:09:18.158 --> 1:09:19.993
- Y'all stay warm, all right?
- Bye.

1:09:23.997 --> 1:09:26.917
- Three quarters of a million.
- Not bad.

1:09:33.465 --> 1:09:34.466
Now what?

1:09:35.175 --> 1:09:38.386
I'm gonna go home. I'm gonna get my stuff.

1:09:38.386 --> 1:09:43.225
And I'm gonna tell him
that I have a sick aunt in Jersey.

1:09:43.225 --> 1:09:45.853
And I'm out first thing in the morning.

1:09:47.854 --> 1:09:49.064
You love me?

1:09:51.399 --> 1:09:52.609
Unfortunately.

1:10:19.094 --> 1:10:20.095
Hey.

1:10:20.095 --> 1:10:23.974
<i>Hey. So...</i>

1:10:23.974 --> 1:10:26.768
I have some good news and some bad news.

1:10:27.352 --> 1:10:30.480
<i>The good news is the money is all yours.</i>

1:10:31.523 --> 1:10:33.275
Okay. What's the bad news?

1:10:38.739 --> 1:10:41.992
The bad news is you were right.

1:10:42.784 --> 1:10:43.785
<i>Right about what?</i>

1:10:47.372 --> 1:10:48.749
The old man loves me.

1:10:49.875 --> 1:10:53.086
<i>He wants to marry me, so I'm staying.</i>

1:10:53.086 --> 1:10:54.421
What are you talking about?

1:10:55.756 --> 1:10:58.425
<i>Maybe I don't wanna
sit around in a bar all day</i>

1:10:58.425 --> 1:11:00.427
pulling short cons
for the rest of my life.

1:11:00.969 --> 1:11:02.346
<i>You can't be serious.</i>

1:11:02.930 --> 1:11:05.140
Sooner or later the old man
is gonna ask questions.

1:11:05.140 --> 1:11:07.518
<i>No. No, he won't. He's too invested.</i>

1:11:08.018 --> 1:11:10.562
He's got too much on his mind.

1:11:10.562 --> 1:11:12.356
You know, his health and his business.

1:11:12.356 --> 1:11:14.858
And that-- that emotional wreck of a son.

1:11:16.443 --> 1:11:18.904
But I'm the good thing, right?

1:11:19.613 --> 1:11:21.365
<i>I'm the good thing he's got.</i>

1:11:21.365 --> 1:11:22.366
Yeah.

