1:22:25.779 --> 1:22:28.365
- I wanna help you with this.
- I get that. I'm just saying that

1:22:28.365 --> 1:22:30.993
- I can find my own apartment. Thank you.
- Why are you getting upset?

1:22:30.993 --> 1:22:32.244
- I'm not.
- No, you are.

1:22:32.244 --> 1:22:34.037
- No, I'm not. I'm just--
- You totally are getting upset.

1:22:34.037 --> 1:22:36.290
- You can't come here and do this...
- No, but I want to.

1:22:36.290 --> 1:22:37.666
- ...and expect me not to react.
- I wanna be a part of this.

1:22:37.666 --> 1:22:41.211
- It's not your problem. You're not my mom!
- No, you're right. I'm not.

1:22:41.211 --> 1:22:43.547
'Cause if I were, I'd tell you
to grow the fuck up.

1:22:48.468 --> 1:22:51.263
People get their hearts broken every day.

1:22:51.263 --> 1:22:53.473
It happens to everybody, okay?

1:22:55.309 --> 1:22:56.310
All the time.

1:22:58.103 --> 1:23:02.149
But most kids aren't entitled enough
to hire men to find the girl who did it.

1:23:02.149 --> 1:23:03.317
She stole money from me.

1:23:03.317 --> 1:23:05.819
That's not why you're doing it.
You want to see her again.

1:23:06.737 --> 1:23:07.738
Right?

1:23:10.908 --> 1:23:13.035
You can lie to yourself,
but you can't lie to me.

1:23:20.209 --> 1:23:21.919
I'm sorry. That was harsh.

1:23:21.919 --> 1:23:23.545
- You think I'm a loser.
- No, I don't.

1:23:23.545 --> 1:23:25.464
- Yeah, you do.
- No, I don't think that you're a loser.

1:23:25.464 --> 1:23:26.632
I think that...

1:23:29.468 --> 1:23:30.802
I think that you're human.

1:23:33.096 --> 1:23:36.475
I think we're all human.

1:23:36.475 --> 1:23:38.101
We're just doing the best we can.

1:23:43.565 --> 1:23:45.150
I'll have Braddock call it off.

1:23:48.946 --> 1:23:52.074
Good for you, sweetheart.
I know it's hard.

1:23:55.369 --> 1:23:58.413
<i>This apartment is unlisted.
